---
// Vendor-page footer. Same structure + disclaimer notes as Footer.astro,
// reframed for the solar-vendor audience (the reader is the installer; the
// building owner is "their client").
import logo from "../../assets/energy-plus-logo.png";
const year = new Date().getFullYear();
---

<footer class="site-footer">
  <div class="container site-footer__inner">
    <div class="site-footer__brand">
      <span class="footer-lockup">
        <img class="footer-lockup__logo" src={logo.src} width="104" height="30" alt="Energy Plus" />
        <span class="footer-lockup__div" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        <span class="wordmark__hotels">Partners</span>
      </span>
      <p class="site-footer__line">
        The efficiency engine behind solar vendors. We diagnose the building,
        verify the savings, and shrink the load so your array sells itself.
      </p>
    </div>

    <nav class="site-footer__nav" aria-label="Footer">
      <a href="#sizing">The math</a>
      <a href="#why-deals-die">Why deals die</a>
      <a href="#procurement">The engineer</a>
      <a href="#profit">Your margin</a>
      <a href="#proof">Proof</a>
      <a href="#book">Become a Partner</a>
    </nav>
  </div>

  <div class="container" id="disclaimers">
    <p class="site-footer__legal">
      <strong>How to read this page.</strong> Energy Plus is an independent
      energy solutions partner. We do not manufacture equipment. We diagnose
      each building and procure, size, and integrate the right efficiency
      technologies from our stack so a solar vendor can offer a complete
      solution. The numbered notes below apply to the marked figures and
      statements throughout this page.
    </p>
    <ol class="site-footer__notes">
      <li id="disc-results">
        <strong>1. Savings, sizing, and performance figures.</strong> All
        savings, load-reduction, system-sizing, payback, equipment-life, and
        bill-reduction figures shown (including ranges such as 20&ndash;30% and
        8&ndash;14%) are illustrative estimates or results achieved at specific
        facilities under their own conditions. They are not predictions or
        guarantees of your clients' results. Array-sizing reductions depend on
        the building's load profile after efficiency measures, local solar
        resource, and design assumptions. Case studies reflect results with
        specific technologies we deploy. Actual results depend on the building,
        climate, occupancy, equipment condition, and utility rates, which is
        exactly why we measure the floor at the meter before anyone commits.
        Modeled numbers are directional estimates, not quotes.
      </li>
      <li id="disc-terms">
        <strong>2. Partnership terms and eligibility.</strong> Our white-label
        and co-sell partner program, including margin, pricing, and contract
        terms, is offered case-by-case and depends on factors such as deal
        volume, the markets you serve, and the size of the buildings'
        electricity bills. "No cost," "the diagnosis is on us," and "nothing
        owed" describe the diagnosis and pilot phase for qualifying buildings;
        they do not describe the cost of any installed solution. Eligibility,
        scheduling, and availability are determined during the partner
        application process.
      </li>
      <li id="disc-tax">
        <strong>3. Tax incentives.</strong> Section 179D and any tax figures
        are potential amounts based on current federal rules and assumptions;
        they are not tax advice. Actual deductions depend on the building, the
        work performed, and the taxpayer's situation. Consult a qualified tax
        advisor.
      </li>
      <li id="disc-utility">
        <strong>4. Utility and incentive programs.</strong> Utility-program
        coverage (for example, "up to 75%," or the state percentages shown in
        the calculator) varies by state, utility, and program, and is subject to
        program availability, funding, and qualification. Amounts shown are
        illustrative and are not guaranteed.
      </li>
    </ol>
  </div>

  <div class="container site-footer__meta">
    <span>&copy; {year} Energy Plus</span>
    <span class="site-footer__neutral">Independent Energy Solutions Partner.</span>
  </div>
</footer>
